sql:
SELECT description 
FROM course_descriptions 
WHERE course_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "sailed smoothly into the harbor" metaphorically refers to the course having no students on the waitlist;
- "sailors waiting to board" refers to students on the waitlist;
- "filled their sails with at least thirty crew members" means the course has an enrollment count of thirty or more students.

'deal with African and African American Studies' refers to the department named 'African and African American Studies';
'class identifiers' represents the combination of the class number, mnemonic, and course number;
'schedule times' refers to the start and end times of the class sessions.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT c.*
FROM courses c
INNER JOIN waitlists w ON c.course_id = w.course_id;

external_knowledge:
- "teachers standing at the helm of the knowledge vessels" refers to instructors teaching courses;
- "the intrepid learner, marked by the number one" refers to the student with student_id 1;
- "academic voyage" metaphorically represents the journey of learning through various courses.

sql:
SELECT s.name, s.email
FROM students s
JOIN waitlists w ON s.student_id = w.student_id;
